Sixty people were on Saturday morning injured in a road accident at Nomotio area along Baragoi-Maralal road, Samburu central sub-county.The victims were travelling in a lorry from Nomotio to Ng&rsquo;ari area, about ten kilometres away for a political rally when the accident occurred.Joseph Longu&rsquo;on, a victim said the driver lost control when he approached a corner.&ldquo;The vehicle was being driven at a high speed when we approached a sharp corner. The vehicle veered off the road and fell into a ditch after the driver failed to control it,&rdquo; he said.A number of passengers were rushed to Samburu County Referral hospital with serious injuries where they have been admitted in two wards and receiving treatment.Joseph Lesilele, a resident of Nomotio said the morning journey caught residents by surprise in their homes.&ldquo;People were busy in their farms, they had to abandon what they were doing after a lorry approached abruptly asking them to attend a political rally,&rdquo; he said.Lesila said most of the accident victims are poor and don&rsquo;t have NHIF cards. he said they were going for the rally to get handouts from politicians.&ldquo;Let politicians look for you at your homes because you are the ones who have votes,&rdquo; he urged.Efforts to reach police for a comment were in futile as Maralal OCPD Abagarro Guyo had travelled to Nairobi on official duties.The accident happened barely hours after twenty people died after a bus collided with two trailers at Mbaruk area, near Gilgil along Nakuru-Nairobi highway.Nakuru police commander Hassan Barua said the driver of the bus was overtaking a truck when he collided with an oncoming truck.Read: 20 dead, several injured in Nakuru-Nairobi accident